WEBVTT

00:03.067 --> 00:04.634
SARAH:
Wait a minute. Excuse me.

00:04.634 --> 00:06.701
But how is a road trip
to Mexico a rite of passage?

00:06.701 --> 00:08.601
Are you getting this, Julia?
You know what?

00:08.601 --> 00:10.267
I say just be supportive
and wave adios

00:10.267 --> 00:11.868
so the two of them
will shut up already

00:11.868 --> 00:13.067
and hit the highway.

00:13.067 --> 00:14.167
Send me a postcard.

00:14.167 --> 00:15.501
WILL: Glad to.
No, no.

00:15.501 --> 00:17.834
This is not about postcards,
Will.

00:17.834 --> 00:19.968
This is not about
documenting an experience.

00:19.968 --> 00:21.634
It's about having one.

00:21.634 --> 00:25.000
It's about driving too fast
and partying too late and--

00:25.000 --> 00:27.501
And sleeping too long
and living too hard.

00:27.501 --> 00:29.267
Damn, he's good.
No, no, no, no, no.

00:29.267 --> 00:31.868
He's just seen
way too many beer commercials.

00:31.868 --> 00:34.167
Because there comes a time
in every man's life

00:34.167 --> 00:35.834
when he has to sit on a beach

00:35.834 --> 00:38.501
and take stock of where
he's been and where he's going.

00:38.501 --> 00:41.300
There comes a time when he just
has to take a deep breath

00:41.300 --> 00:42.434
and swallow the worm.

00:42.434 --> 00:44.834
SARAH:
Swallow the worm?
Is that a metaphor?

00:44.834 --> 00:46.634
WILL:
A tequila reference, actually.

00:46.634 --> 00:48.501
SARAH: Oh.
Hey, Jule.

00:50.434 --> 00:52.167
Griffin?

00:53.534 --> 00:55.734
Uh, hey,

00:58.100 --> 01:00.133
I-I don't understand. When--?
A few days ago.

01:00.133 --> 01:02.000
Ah.

01:02.000 --> 01:04.700
Uh, how you been?
You look...

01:04.700 --> 01:06.968
I didn't hear from you.
You--

01:06.968 --> 01:09.000
Didn't you get
my letters at school?

01:09.000 --> 01:11.100
Your letters?
Mm-hm.

01:11.100 --> 01:12.868
Um, no, no. I--

01:12.868 --> 01:14.634
See, no, no,
as soon as I'd done my time

01:14.634 --> 01:18.267
and my term was over, I was--
I was outta the place.

01:18.267 --> 01:20.367
My roommate's old man's got, uh,

01:20.367 --> 01:22.167
this shipping operation
down in Florida.

01:22.167 --> 01:23.667
He got me this
merchant marine gig.

01:23.667 --> 01:25.200
My boat's--

01:25.200 --> 01:26.701
[SIGHS]

01:26.701 --> 01:28.267
I just got back from Bangkok.

01:29.400 --> 01:31.200
They got weird food
in Bangkok.

01:31.200 --> 01:32.701
[CHUCKLES]

01:32.701 --> 01:36.200
Um,
you didn't call or anything.

01:36.200 --> 01:37.467
N-no.

01:37.467 --> 01:38.667
Um,

01:38.667 --> 01:40.234
I thought about it.

01:40.234 --> 01:42.567
I decided it would
be a bad idea, you know,

01:42.567 --> 01:44.734
c-considering how things are
with you and Justin.

01:44.734 --> 01:46.167
We broke up.

01:46.167 --> 01:49.868
Uh, Justin and me,
l-last s-spring,

01:49.868 --> 01:51.100
I-I wrote you.

01:51.100 --> 01:52.667
I wro--
I wrote you all about it.

01:52.667 --> 01:56.634
Wow.
You broke up?

01:57.834 --> 01:59.000
Yeah.

02:00.901 --> 02:02.267
I didn't know.

02:04.968 --> 02:06.367
[CHUCKLES]

02:06.367 --> 02:08.167
I can't believe it's you.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.934
[THE BODEANS' "CLOSER TO FIVE"
PLAYING]

02:16.067 --> 02:18.934
 <i>* Everybody wants to live *</i>

02:18.934 --> 02:20.501
